Two women communicate at a meeting:
The first:
- How are you, how are you?
The second:
It's just great. My lover promised to buy me a chinchilla fur coat!
First:
- Amazing!
The second:
- He also said he would buy me a Bentley.
First:
- Amazing!
The second:
- And the other day we're going on vacation to the Maldives!
First
- Amazing!
The second:
- Well, what's new with you?
First:
- And I study at the school of good manners.
The second:
- And what did you learn there, what good manners?
First:
- Well, in the last lesson, for example, we were taught to replace the phrase NOT N%ZDI! The phrase is AMAZING.
